           Summary        
                                    
                                       
                                                                 
        Discover a prehistoric watering hole where multiple           
        dinosaur species fought to the death under the intense heat   
        of a Jurassic drought. Watch as more than 15,000 bones are    
        uncovered at the scene of one of the bloodiest battles in     
        Paleohistory. Scientists are able to identify Allosaurus      
        and its rival Ceratosaurus as the predators. Evidence         
        collected at the site, detailed animal behaviors, and the     
        results of hi-tech CAT scanning are used to recreate what     
         happened on this dry lakebed in Utah 150 million years ago.
